classitems.description:
Usage: Initialize(w, h);
----------------------------------
Initialize the engine. Creates the default parmetric surfaces.

Usage: OnFingerDown(l);
----------------------------------
Starts a gesture, rotation.

Usage: OnFingerDown(ld, ln);
----------------------------------
continue a gesture, rotation.

Usage: Zoom(z);
----------------------------------
Sets a new zoom radius.

Usage: Render();
----------------------------------
renders one frame.

Usage: ChangeSurface(3);
----------------------------------
Sets a new parametric surface.

Usage: i = GetVertexCount();
----------------------------------
Returns the number of vertex of the parametric surface.

Usage: i = GetLineIndexCount();
----------------------------------
Returns the number of lines of the parametric surface.

Usage: i = GetTriangleIndexCount();
----------------------------------
Returns the number of triangles of the parametric surface.

Usage: GenerateVertices(vertices, flags);
----------------------------------
Generates the vertices of the surface.

Usage: GenerateLineIndices(indices);
----------------------------------
Generates the line indexes of the surface.

Usage: GenerateTriangleIndices(vertices);
----------------------------------
Generates the triangle indexes of the surface.

Usage: Zoom(newRadius);
----------------------------------
change the zoom of the surface.

Usage:  InitializeProgramData();
----------------------------------
Initialize all OpenGL requiered variables for our shaders.

Usage:  SetEye();
----------------------------------
Sets the eye position to the vertex shader, we need this to do the raytrace.

Usage:  UpdateColor(r,g,b);
----------------------------------
Updates the primary color rgb of the algebraic surface render.

Usage:  UpdateColor2(r,g,b);
----------------------------------
Updates the secondary color rgb of the algebraic surface render.

Usage:  UpdateRadius(r);
----------------------------------
Updates the radius value we pass to the shader for intersection.

Usage:  setConstant();
----------------------------------
Sets constanst values in OpenGL, like lights.

Usage:  GenerateArrays();
----------------------------------
Generates vertices array space in OpenGL.

Usage: resize( w, h );
----------------------------------
Resize OpenGl ViewPort.

Usage: display( w, h );
----------------------------------
Renders one frame.

Usage: expressionT myTree; PreOrder( myTree );
--------------------------------------
prints the tree in PreOrder.

Usage: EvalExp( myTree, 0);
--------------------------------------
Creates the shader code for the surface.

Usage: EvalExpNoCode( myTree, 0);
--------------------------------------
Creates the expression for the surface.

Usage: EvalDegree(myTree);
--------------------------------------
returns the degree of the algebraic surface.

Usage: i = getCodeLeng();
--------------------------------------
Returns the length of  the algebraic surface generated.

Usage: EvalDerivate( myTree);
--------------------------------------
Creates shader code for the algebraic surface partial derivatives.

Usage: EvalDerivateNoCode( myTree);
--------------------------------------
Creates the expression for the algebraic surface partial derivatives.

Usage: getDegree();
--------------------------------------
returns the degree of the algebraic surface.

Usage: if(ErrorExist()) string = getErrorMsg();
--------------------------------------
if there was an error call this to get the message.

Usage: ParseError(msg);
--------------------------------------
To be call to raise an error.

Usage: FreeScanner(scanner);
----------------------------
This function frees the storage associated with scanner.

Usage: len = StringLength(s);
-----------------------------
This function returns the length of s.
